		,"year":1959,"typ":"J","ref":"J,PR","vol":"114","p":"571"
		,"shortRef":"Jour: Physical Review, Vol.114, p.571 (1959)"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" The"
		,"absolute cross section was determined in two ways:"
		,"1. Absolute determination of the cross section was made"
		,"by integrating the angular distribution (see Subent"
		,"003) taken at a proton energy of 2.265 MeV and"
		,"equating the integral to the total cross section as"
		,"measured by Macklin, etc. at this energy."
		,"2. The absolute cross section was determined at a"
		,"proton energy of 2.265 MeV at 0. degr. (counter angle"
		,"0.-6. degr.) by comparison of the yield from a weighted"
		,"LiF target with a standard Ra-Be source calibrated by"
		,"the National Bureau of Standards."]
	}
